title: Flying LOW Over Chicago Midway Int'l Airport! (Cessna 172 with ATC audio)

media:group.media:title: Flying LOW Over Chicago Midway Int'l Airport! (Cessna 172 with ATC audio)
media:group.media:description:
Fabian pilots the Cessna 172 with his cameraboy Jeeves.
- Support an aspiring pilot (promo code: AFP): https://midwestmodelstore.com?sca_ref=1601682.9MDG0Hpt01
- Follow Fabian: http://www.instagram.com/thepilotfabian
- Follow Jeeves: http://www.instagram.com/Airforceproud_95

Huge thank you to Fabian for making this video possible!
- Our last video (737 sim): https://youtu.be/9g3068Tw9hs

We depart the Romeoville Airport (KLEW) and proceed VFR directly over Chicago Midway Int'l (KMDW). We fly the Chicago Lakeshore VFR corridor past the city skyline before returning home where Fabian absolutely butters the bread on runway 27. Despite the moderate turbulence and my resting bitchface, I thoroughly enjoyed this experience.
